<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="53">
Wilson (2003) took a broad view of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33959" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radoszkowskii">Pheidole radoszkowskii</taxonomicName>
and synonymized several names, including Santschi’s 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151512" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii reflexans Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="radoszkowskii" variety="reflexans">variety reflexans</taxonomicName>
. The evidence for resurrecting 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151512" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii reflexans Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reflexans">P. reflexans</taxonomicName>
to species is strong, however. Both 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33959" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radoszkowskii">P. radoszkowskii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151512" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii reflexans Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reflexans">P. reflexans</taxonomicName>
are locally sympatric across eastern Paraguay, with the former species commonly found in open habitats such as campo cerrado, roadside, and pasture, while the later is restricted to closed forests. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151512" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii reflexans Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reflexans">Pheidole reflexans</taxonomicName>
can be one of the most common forest-floor ants and is frequently recovered in sifted litter samples from subtropical tall forests. The morphological differences between the two forms are consistent across eastern Paraguay. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151512" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii reflexans Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reflexans">Pheidole reflexans</taxonomicName>
is more gracile, with considerably longer legs and antennal scapes, and in Paraguay is also somewhat more pilose in the major caste, supporting&gt; 10 suberect setae on gastric tergite 1 (= abd. tergite 4). This pilosity difference appears to be regional, as Mayr’s 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33959" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole radoszkowskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radoszkowskii">P. radoszkowskii</taxonomicName>
types from French Guiana (NHMW, examined) are more pilose than the Paraguayan populations of the same species.
</paragraph>
